42 760 Td
(Example A: 7-day moving average) Tj
T*
(SMA_7 = \(100+102+101+104+106+105+107\)/7 = 725/7 = 103.57) Tj
T*
(Meaning: average recent level is 103.57, which smooths daily noise.) Tj
T*
T*
(Example B: daily change for momentum) Tj
T*
(delta on Day7 = C_7 - C_6 = 107 - 105 = +2) Tj
T*
(Positive delta means upward movement on latest day.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(4\) METRIC 1: moving_avg_7d) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Formula:) Tj
T*
(moving_avg_7d\(t\) = average of last 7 close values) Tj
T*
(Code equivalent:) Tj
T*
(F.mean\('close'\).over\(window_7\)) Tj
T*
(Why we use it:) Tj
T*
(- Fast trend signal for short-term direction.) Tj
T*
(- Helps model see if price is persistently rising/falling.) Tj
T*
(How to interpret:) Tj
T*
(- If current close > moving_avg_7d, short-term tone is usually stronger.) Tj
T*
(- If current close < moving_avg_7d, short-term tone may be weaker.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(5\) METRIC 2: sma_50 and sma_200) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Formula:) Tj
T*
(sma_50\(t\)  = average of last 50 closes) Tj
T*
(sma_200\(t\) = average of last 200 closes) Tj
T*
(Why we use them:) Tj
T*
(- sma_50 captures medium trend.) Tj
T*
(- sma_200 captures long trend \(strategic context\).) Tj
T*
(How to interpret \(simple\):) Tj
T*
(- Bullish structure often when sma_50 > sma_200.) Tj
T*
(- Weak structure often when sma_50 < sma_200.) Tj
T*
(Project behavior:) Tj
T*
(- Rows where sma_50 is null are dropped \(not enough history yet\).) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(6\) METRIC 3: volatility_7d) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Formula:) Tj
T*
(volatility_7d = standard deviation of last 7 closes) Tj
T*
(Code equivalent:) Tj
T*
(F.stddev\('close'\).over\(window_7\)) Tj
T*
(Why we use it:) Tj
T*
(- Measures instability/risk in recent price behavior.) Tj
T*
(Worked intuition:) Tj
T*
(- Prices [100,101,100,101,100,101,100] => low volatility) Tj
ET
endstream
