(- Prices [95,105,96,106,94,107,93] => high volatility) Tj
T*
(How to interpret:) Tj
T*
(- Higher value = bigger swings = harder prediction environment.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(7\) METRIC 4: ema_20 \(implementation note\)) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(What code does now:) Tj
T*
(ema_20 is set to 20-day simple average \(SMA_20\) in current code.) Tj
T*
(Why still useful:) Tj
T*
(- It still gives a 20-day smoothed trend line.) Tj
T*
(- Works well as a practical trend feature for model and dashboard.) Tj
T*
(Note for advanced users:) Tj
T*
(- Classic EMA gives more weight to recent prices.) Tj
T*
(- We can upgrade this in future versions.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(8\) METRIC 5: MACD and MACD Signal) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Project formulas:) Tj
T*
(macd\(t\) = SMA_12\(t\) - SMA_26\(t\)) Tj
T*
(macd_signal\(t\) = SMA_9\(macd\)) Tj
T*
(Why we use them:) Tj
T*
(- Momentum and trend acceleration indicator.) Tj
T*
(Simple worked example:) Tj
T*
(If SMA_12 = 108 and SMA_26 = 103, macd = +5) Tj
T*
(Positive MACD means short window is above medium window.) Tj
T*
(If MACD crosses above macd_signal, momentum is improving.) Tj
T*
(Interpretation tip:) Tj
T*
(- Sign \(+/-\) tells direction bias.) Tj
T*
(- Distance from signal line suggests strength of momentum change.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(9\) METRIC 6: Bollinger Bands \(bb_upper, bb_lower\)) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Formulas:) Tj
T*
(bb_upper = SMA_20 + 2 * SD_20) Tj
T*
(bb_lower = SMA_20 - 2 * SD_20) Tj
T*
(Why we use them:) Tj
T*
(- Dynamic range based on current volatility.) Tj
T*
(- Detects potentially stretched moves.) Tj
T*
(Worked example:) Tj
T*
(If SMA_20 = 100 and SD_20 = 4:) Tj
T*
(bb_upper = 100 + 2*4 = 108) Tj
T*
(bb_lower = 100 - 2*4 = 92) Tj
T*
(If close is 109, price is above upper band \(overextended zone\).) Tj
T*
(If close is 91, price is below lower band \(oversold zone\).) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
