(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(10\) METRIC 7: RSI \(rsi_14\)) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Steps used in code:) Tj
T*
(1. delta_t = C_t - C_\(t-1\)) Tj
T*
(2. gain_t = max\(delta_t, 0\)) Tj
T*
(3. loss_t = max\(-delta_t, 0\)) Tj
T*
(4. avg_gain_14 = average of gains over 14 days) Tj
T*
(5. avg_loss_14 = average of losses over 14 days) Tj
T*
(6. RS = avg_gain_14 / avg_loss_14) Tj
T*
(7. RSI = 100 - \(100 / \(1 + RS\)\)) Tj
T*
(Why we use RSI:) Tj
T*
(- Standard momentum oscillator with easy interpretation.) Tj
T*
(- Useful for identifying overbought/oversold conditions.) Tj
T*
(Simple worked example:) Tj
T*
(Suppose avg_gain_14 = 1.2 and avg_loss_14 = 0.6) Tj
T*
(RS = 1.2 / 0.6 = 2) Tj
T*
(RSI = 100 - 100/\(1+2\) = 100 - 33.33 = 66.67) Tj
T*
(Interpretation:) Tj
T*
(- RSI around 67 means strong momentum, not yet extreme overbought.) Tj
T*
(Typical ranges:) Tj
T*
(- >70 often called overbought) Tj
T*
(- <30 often called oversold) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(11\) METRIC 8: ATR \(atr_14\)) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(True Range per day:) Tj
T*
(TR1 = H_t - L_t) Tj
T*
(TR2 = abs\(H_t - PrevClose_t\)) Tj
T*
(TR3 = abs\(L_t - PrevClose_t\)) Tj
T*
(TR  = max\(TR1, TR2, TR3\)) Tj
T*
(ATR formula:) Tj
T*
(atr_14 = average\(TR over last 14 days\)) Tj
T*
(Why we use ATR:) Tj
T*
(- Captures intraday range and gap risk.) Tj
T*
(- Better risk gauge than close-only volatility in many markets.) Tj
T*
(Worked example:) Tj
T*
(If H=110, L=104, PrevClose=107:) Tj
T*
(TR1=6, TR2=3, TR3=3, so TR=6) Tj
T*
(If average TR over 14 days is 5.2, then ATR=5.2) Tj
T*
(Interpretation:) Tj
T*
(- Higher ATR means wider typical movement and higher position risk.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(12\) METRIC 9: Stochastic Oscillator \(stoch_k, stoch_d\)) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Formulas:) Tj
ET
endstream
