42 760 Td
(lowest_low_14  = min\(low over last 14 days\)) Tj
T*
(highest_high_14 = max\(high over last 14 days\)) Tj
T*
(stoch_k = \(\(Close - lowest_low_14\) / \(highest_high_14 - lowest_low_14\)\) * 100) Tj
T*
(stoch_d = 3-day average of stoch_k) Tj
T*
(Why we use it:) Tj
T*
(- Shows where close sits inside recent high-low range.) Tj
T*
(Worked example:) Tj
T*
(If Close=107, lowest_low_14=95, highest_high_14=110:) Tj
T*
(stoch_k = \(\(107-95\)/\(110-95\)\)*100 = \(12/15\)*100 = 80) Tj
T*
(If last 3 stoch_k values are 70, 80, 75 => stoch_d = 75) Tj
T*
(Interpretation:) Tj
T*
(- High values \(near 100\): close near range high.) Tj
T*
(- Low values \(near 0\): close near range low.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(13\) HOW ALL METRICS WORK TOGETHER) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(No single metric is enough. We combine them to reduce false signals.) Tj
T*
(Example combined read:) Tj
T*
(- Trend strong: close > sma_50 > sma_200) Tj
T*
(- Momentum strong: macd > macd_signal and RSI in healthy range) Tj
T*
(- Risk acceptable: volatility_7d and ATR not extreme) Tj
T*
(This combination usually gives better confidence than any single indicator.) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(14\) HOW THIS CONNECTS TO PRODUCT SIGNALS) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(These silver metrics are fed into ML models \(1y and 5y horizons\).) Tj
T*
(The model returns probabilities \(confidence\).) Tj
T*
(Strategy thresholds convert probabilities to labels such as:) Tj
T*
(INVEST NOW, ACCUMULATE, MONITOR, WAIT, AVOID, STRONG HOLD.) Tj
T*
T*
(So silver layer = the mathematical foundation behind all downstream outputs:) Tj
T*
(- dashboard insights) Tj
T*
(- API responses) Tj
T*
(- email reports) Tj
T*
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(15\) COMMON BEGINNER QUESTIONS) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(Q1: Why not use only price?) Tj
T*
(A: Price alone does not separate trend, momentum, and risk. Multiple views are safer.) Tj
T*
T*
(Q2: Are these formulas guaranteed to predict returns?) Tj
T*
(A: No. They improve decision context but cannot remove market uncertainty.) Tj
T*
T*
(Q3: Why does model still make mistakes?) Tj
T*
(A: Markets change regimes, data has noise, and indicators are probabilistic signals.) Tj
ET
endstream
